xylanIpxStaticRouteTable.name: xylanIpxStaticRouteTable
xylanIpxStaticRouteTable.description: The Static Routes table contains information about all destinations reached via statically configured routes.

xylanIpxStaticRouteEntry.name: xylanIpxStaticRouteEntry
xylanIpxStaticRouteEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one static route.

xylanIpxStaticRouteNetNum.name: xylanIpxStaticRouteNetNum
xylanIpxStaticRouteNetNum.description: The IPX network number of the route's destination.

xylanIpxStaticRouteAdminState.name: xylanIpxStaticRouteAdminState
xylanIpxStaticRouteAdminState.description: The current status of this route. active (1) means the route is functioning, delete (2) tell SNMP to delete the route

xylanIpxStaticRouteNextHopNet.name: xylanIpxStaticRouteNextHopNet
xylanIpxStaticRouteNextHopNet.description: The IPX network number of the router used to reach the first hop in the static route.

xylanIpxStaticRouteNextHopNode.name: xylanIpxStaticRouteNextHopNode
xylanIpxStaticRouteNextHopNode.description: The IPX node number of the router used to reach the first hop in the static route.

xylanIpxStaticRouteTicks.name: xylanIpxStaticRouteTicks
xylanIpxStaticRouteTicks.description: The delay, in ticks, to reach the route's destination.

xylanIpxStaticRouteHopCount.name: xylanIpxStaticRouteHopCount
xylanIpxStaticRouteHopCount.description: The number of hops necessary to reach the destination.

xylanIpxRipSapFilterTable.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterTable
xylanIpxRipSapFilterTable.description: The IPX Rip/Sap Filter Table contains information about all filters that have been defined.

xylanIpxRipSapFilterEntry.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterEntry
xylanIpxRipSapFilterEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one filter.

xylanIpxRipSapFilterNum.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterNum
xylanIpxRipSapFilterNum.description: The number identifying this instance. This number can be used when specifying a filter to delete.

xylanIpxRipSapFilterAdminState.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterAdminState
xylanIpxRipSapFilterAdminState.description: The current status of this filter, active (1) means the filter is functioning, delete (2) tells SNMP to delete the filter

xylanIpxRipSapFilterNet.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterNet
xylanIpxRipSapFilterNet.description: The IPX Network Address to filter. A network address of all 0's is used to denote All Networks.

xylanIpxRipSapFilterNetMask.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterNetMask
xylanIpxRipSapFilterNetMask.description: The IPX Network Mask to be used.

xylanIpxRipSapFilterNode.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterNode
xylanIpxRipSapFilterNode.description: The IPX node address to filter. A node address of all 0's is used to denote All Nodes.

xylanIpxRipSapFilterNodeMask.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterNodeMask
xylanIpxRipSapFilterNodeMask.description: The IPX node address mask to be used.

xylanIpxRipSapFilterSvcType.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterSvcType
xylanIpxRipSapFilterSvcType.description: The SAP service type on which to filter. The SAP service types are defined by Novell. A value of ALL (65535) indicates that all services will be filtered.

xylanIpxRipSapFilterMode.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterMode
xylanIpxRipSapFilterMode.description: The action defined by this filter. block (1) means packets matching this filter will be blocked, and allow (0) means that packets matching this filter will be allowed.

xylanIpxRipSapFilterGroupId.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterGroupId
xylanIpxRipSapFilterGroupId.description: The GroupId can be used to apply this filter to a particular interface. A GroupId of 0 means that the filter is global.

xylanIpxRipSapFilterWanType.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterWanType
xylanIpxRipSapFilterWanType.description: If the Vlan has Wan Routing enabled, this object can be used to specify whether this interface is a Frame Relay service or a PPP service. This will be used to determine whether the slot/port/vc or PeerId fields are applicable to this entry. A value of 1 implies that this field is not used. (The interface is not a WAN interface or the filter is not being applied to a specific VC or PeerId.) A value of 2 indicates that this is a Frame Relay service in which case the slot/port/vc fields can be used to apply the filter to a specific VC. A value of 3 indicates that this is a PPP service and the Peer ID field may be used.

xylanIpxRipSapFilterSlot.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterSlot
xylanIpxRipSapFilterSlot.description: If the WanType specifies a Frame Relay service, the slot/port/vc can be used to apply this filter to a particular Virtual Circuit (VC).

xylanIpxRipSapFilterPort.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterPort
xylanIpxRipSapFilterPort.description: If the WanType specifies a Frame Relay service, the slot/port/vc can be used to apply this filter to a particular Virtual Circuit (VC).

xylanIpxRipSapFilterVc.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterVc
xylanIpxRipSapFilterVc.description: If the WanType specifies a Frame Relay service, the slot/port/vc can be used to apply this filter to a particular Virtual Circuit (VC).

xylanIpxRipSapFilterPeerId.name: xylanIpxRipSapFilterPeerId
xylanIpxRipSapFilterPeerId.description: If the WanType specifies a PPP service, the PeerId can be used to apply this filter to a particular Peer.

xylanIpxWatchdogSpoofTable.name: xylanIpxWatchdogSpoofTable
xylanIpxWatchdogSpoofTable.description: The IPX Watchdog Spoofing Table contains information about all of the WAN routing services and their current IPX spoofing status.

xylanIpxWatchdogSpoofEntry.name: xylanIpxWatchdogSpoofEntry
xylanIpxWatchdogSpoofEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one WAN routing service.

xylanIpxWatchdogSpoofGroupId.name: xylanIpxWatchdogSpoofGroupId
xylanIpxWatchdogSpoofGroupId.description: The GroupId of the WAN routing service that this entry applies to.

xylanIpxWatchdogSpoofMode.name: xylanIpxWatchdogSpoofMode
xylanIpxWatchdogSpoofMode.description: This controls whether the IPX Watchdog Spoofing is enabled or disabled. When enabled, this routing service will spoof IPX Watchdog packets. When disabled, this routing service will not spoof IPX Watchdog packets.

xylanIpxSerialFilterTable.name: xylanIpxSerialFilterTable
xylanIpxSerialFilterTable.description: The IPX Serialization Filtering Table contains information about all of the WAN routing services and their current IPX Serialization Filtering status.

xylanIpxSerialFilterEntry.name: xylanIpxSerialFilterEntry
xylanIpxSerialFilterEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one WAN routing service.

xylanIpxSerialFilterGroupId.name: xylanIpxSerialFilterGroupId
xylanIpxSerialFilterGroupId.description: The GroupId of the WAN routing service that this entry applies to.

xylanIpxSerialFilterMode.name: xylanIpxSerialFilterMode
xylanIpxSerialFilterMode.description: This controls whether the IPX Serialization Filtering is enabled or disabled. When enabled, this routing service will filter IPX Serialization packets. When disabled, this routing service will not filter IPX Serialization packets.

xylanSpxKeepaliveSpoofTable.name: xylanSpxKeepaliveSpoofTable
xylanSpxKeepaliveSpoofTable.description: The SPX Keepalive Spoofing Table contains information about all of the WAN routing services and their current SPX Keepalive spoofing status.

xylanSpxKeepaliveSpoofEntry.name: xylanSpxKeepaliveSpoofEntry
xylanSpxKeepaliveSpoofEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one WAN routing service.

xylanSpxKeepaliveSpoofGroupId.name: xylanSpxKeepaliveSpoofGroupId
xylanSpxKeepaliveSpoofGroupId.description: The GroupId of the WAN routing service that this entry applies to.

xylanSpxKeepaliveSpoofMode.name: xylanSpxKeepaliveSpoofMode
xylanSpxKeepaliveSpoofMode.description: This controls whether the SPX Keepalive Spoofing is enabled or disabled. When enabled, this routing service will spoof SPX Keepalive packets. When disabled, this routing service will not spoof SPX Keepalive packets.

xylanIpxType20Table.name: xylanIpxType20Table
xylanIpxType20Table.description: The IPX Type 20 packets allow NetBios to use IPX. This can enable the passing of packet on each interface.

xylanIpxType20Entry.name: xylanIpxType20Entry
xylanIpxType20Entry.description: Each entry corresponds to one Virtual LAN.

xylanIpxType20VlanId.name: xylanIpxType20VlanId
xylanIpxType20VlanId.description: The VLAN Id of the routing interface that this entry applies to.

xylanIpxType20Mode.name: xylanIpxType20Mode
xylanIpxType20Mode.description: This controls whether IPX Type 20 packet are enabled or disabled. When enabled, this routing interface will forward Type 20 packets. When disabled, the packets will not.

xylanIpxTimerTable.name: xylanIpxTimerTable
xylanIpxTimerTable.description: The IPX Timer allows adjustable variation of the RIP and SAP timers.

xylanIpxTimerEntry.name: xylanIpxTimerEntry
xylanIpxTimerEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one Virtual LAN.

xylanIpxTimerVlanId.name: xylanIpxTimerVlanId
xylanIpxTimerVlanId.description: The VLAN Id of the routing interface that this entry applies to.

xylanIpxTimerSap.name: xylanIpxTimerSap
xylanIpxTimerSap.description: This controls whether IPX SAP packet timer duration.

xylanIpxTimerRip.name: xylanIpxTimerRip
xylanIpxTimerRip.description: This controls whether IPX RIP packet timer duration.

xylanIpxDefRouteTable.name: xylanIpxDefRouteTable
xylanIpxDefRouteTable.description: The default route table contains information about the destinations to which all packets are sent when the destination network is not known.

xylanIpxDefRouteEntry.name: xylanIpxDefRouteEntry
xylanIpxDefRouteEntry.description: One table entry per switch for default route.

xylanIpxDefRouteNum.name: xylanIpxDefRouteNum
xylanIpxDefRouteNum.description: The table row ID will always be 1.

xylanIpxDefRouteNet.name: xylanIpxDefRouteNet
xylanIpxDefRouteNet.description: The IPX network number of the router used to reach the first hop in the default route.

xylanIpxDefRouteNode.name: xylanIpxDefRouteNode
xylanIpxDefRouteNode.description: The IPX node number of the router used to reach the first hop in the default route.

xylanIpxExtMsg.name: xylanIpxExtMsg
xylanIpxExtMsg.description: A boolean variable that indicated whether extended RIP/SAP packets are sent and received.
